            "answer_text": "Did people swear during the Middle Ages? Yes: their swearing was more often blasphemy than obscenity, and the use of bodily-function words seems to have been more a question of decorum than taboo. However, there are loads of preachments against swearing by God and the saints, and narratives of people doing just that (e.g. Chaucer\u2019s Pardoner\u2019s Tale). My favourite story is of a noblewoman confessing to her chaplain, who reproves her for her excessive swearing: -My lady, your swearing is a grave offense. You must cease. -By God! I will. ",
